\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Elko County Information Operations Department (ECIO) establishes this policy to define the authority,
 structure,
 and program framework governing the Department's cybersecurity incident response capability.
 This policy is the governing capstone of Chapter 4 (Incident Response) of the ECIO Policy Manual and constitutes the Department's formal cybersecurity incident response program statement for submission to the Nevada state cyber defense office.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy serves two distinct audiences:
 internal personnel and auditors evaluating it within the full context of the ECIO Policy Manual,
 and external reviewers—
including the Nevada state cyber defense office—
who may review it as a standalone document.
 Where this policy references concepts,
 roles,
 or procedures whose authoritative definitions reside elsewhere in the manual,
 it states the operative substance in plain language.
 Those statements are incorporative and do not constitute independent definitions;
 the ECIO Policy Manual's governance framework remains the authoritative source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Chapter 4 Subordination Principle
\series default
.
 Chapter 4 is an explicitly subordinate program framework within the ECIO Policy Manual.
 No policy in Chapter 4 creates an independent authority structure,
 modifies role definitions or authorities established elsewhere in the manual,
 or supersedes any obligation established in Chapters 1 through 3 or Chapter 5.
 Where Chapter 4 references a role,
 timeline,
 classification,
 or procedure established in another policy,
 that reference is incorporative —
 Chapter 4 operates under those established definitions without restating or redefining them.
 This principle is established here once and governs the entire chapter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs the establishment,
 authority,
 structure,
 and program framework of the ECIO cybersecurity incident response capability.
 It applies to all IT systems,
 services,
 and infrastructure operated or managed by the Information Operations Department,
 and to all IT Department personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Governed activities include
\series default
:
 formal declaration of cybersecurity incidents,
 exercise of Incident Commander authority during cybersecurity incidents,
 the IR lifecycle framework used to organize response activity,
 mandatory external reporting obligations,
 and the operational policy roadmap established in Section 6.2.
\end_layout

