\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Incident Reporting
\series default
.
 The CJIS Security Policy establishes a two-part incident reporting obligation.
 First,
 all IT Department personnel shall report any suspected or confirmed security incident to the Incident Commander immediately,
 not to exceed one (1) hour after discovery.
 Second,
 upon the Incident Commander's confirmation of a reportable incident,
 the IT Director,
 acting in the capacity of the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO),
 shall notify the CJIS Systems Officer (CSO),
 the State Identification Bureau (SIB) Chief,
 or the Interface Agency Official as required by CJIS Security Policy Section IR-6.
 The CJIS Security Policy does not attach a specific timer to this external notification obligation;
 it is triggered by confirmation,
 not by the one-hour internal reporting clock.
 This obligation is acknowledged here at the program level.
 Its operational execution —
 including notification mechanics,
 documentation requirements,
 and escalation procedures —
 is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Breach Notification
\series default
.
 Public and stakeholder notification regarding security breaches affecting personal information shall be executed in strict accordance with NRS 603A.220,
 which requires notification in the most expedient time possible following discovery of a breach.
 This obligation is acknowledged here at the program level.
 Its operational execution is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
