\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
External Partner Relationships
\series default
.
 The ECIO maintains active membership in the Multi-State Information Sharing and Analysis Center (MS-ISAC) and the Nevada Information Sharing and Analysis Center (NV-ISAC).
 These memberships provide access to threat intelligence,
 incident coordination resources,
 and analytical support from the broader state and national cybersecurity community.
 The ECIO also maintains working relationships with the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) and the Nevada Department of Public Safety (DPS) for purposes of incident coordination and law enforcement referral.
 The operational procedures governing engagement with these and other external partners are established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Operational Handback
\series default
.
 When the security response phase of a cybersecurity incident concludes —
 that is,
 when the threat has been contained,
 eradicated,
 and the affected environment has been stabilized to a state suitable for operational recovery —
 the Incident Commander shall issue an explicit Operational Handback declaration.
 This declaration marks the transfer of recovery authority from Chapter 4 back to the operational continuity framework governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.15"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Operational Handback shall never be assumed;
 ambiguity is not permitted.
 An incident remains under Chapter 4 authority until the Incident Commander explicitly declares otherwise.
 The full mechanics governing Operational Handback initiation are established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 
\series bold
Policy 
